17/01/2010
ATHENS, Greece -- A bomb went off in front of the information and media ministry in downtown Athens late on Friday (January 15th), according to a police announcement early Saturday. The blast caused material damage but no injuries were reported. The incident came on the heels of a blast outside the parliament building about a week ago. Two leftist terror groups claimed responsibility for that attack. (AP, Reuters, AFP, Net - 16/01/10)
